detailedDescription.articleBody: Diego Armando Maradona is a retired Argentine professional footballer. He has served as a manager and coach at other clubs as well as the national team of Argentina.
Diego Armando Maradona Sinagra is an Italian footballer and beach soccer player, who plays for A.S.D San Giorgio in Italy.

Luciana Paula Aymar is a retired Argentine field hockey player.
She is the only player in history to receive the FIH Player of the Year Award eight times, and she is considered as the best female hockey player of all time.

Diego Pablo Forlán Corazzo is a Uruguayan footballer who plays as a forward for Peñarol. He is a two-time winner of both the Pichichi Trophy and the European Golden Shoe, and also received the Golden Ball as the best player at the 2010 World Cup.
Diego da Silva Costa, is a Spanish professional footballer who plays as a striker for English club Chelsea and the Spain national team.
Diego Pablo Simeone González, also known as Cholo, is an Argentine football manager and former player. He is currently the manager of Spanish La Liga club Atlético de Madrid.
Diego Alberto Milito is an Argentine footballer who plays as a striker for Racing Club and also formerly played for the Argentine national team.
Raúl Alfredo Maradona Franco, also known as Lalo Maradona is an Argentine former professional footballer who played as a striker.
Bogdan Ganev Dochev is a retired Bulgarian football referee. He is known for having refereed two matches in the FIFA World Cup, one in 1982 and one in 1986.
Diego Armando Valentin Contento is a German professional footballer of Italian descent who currently plays as a left back for Girondins de Bordeaux in the Ligue 1.
Hugo Hernán Maradona, also known as El Turco, is an Argentine Association football coach and former player, he is the brother of legendary player Diego Maradona.
Guillermo Coppola is an Argentine businessman. He was born in Buenos Aires in 1948. He worked as the agent of over two hundred football players, and eventually became the agent of Diego Maradona.
Diego Biseswar is a Dutch professional footballer who plays for Turkish club Kayserispor, as a left winger.

Diego Armando Magdaleno is a Mexican-American boxer in the Super Featherweight division and is the current NABF Super Featherweight Champion. He's also the brother of undefeated boxer Jesús Magdaleno. Diego has been featured in the top ten in Ring Magazine's ratings for junior lightweight.
Maradona Rebello is an Indian actor who works in the Bollywood film industry. Rebello's first name was kept by his father after being inspired by the footballer Diego Maradona.

Erik Fredriksson is a former Swedish football referee. He officiated four World Cup games: Yugoslavia v Northern Ireland in 1982; Italy v Bulgaria and USSR v Belgium in 1986; and Argentina v USSR in 1990.
Lionel Andrés "Leo" Messi is an Argentine professional footballer who plays as a forward for Spanish club Barcelona and the Argentina national team.

Juan Manuel Iturbe Arévalos is a Paraguayan professional footballer who plays as a forward for English club Bournemouth, on loan from Italian club Roma.
He represented the Paraguay national team in a friendly match in 2009.

Gerald James was a British actor best known for his character actor roles in British television productions such as The Sandbaggers, The Professionals, Secret Army, Sapphire & Steel, Hadleigh and The Pickwick Papers.
Nompumelelo Nyandeni is a South African football forward who previously played for Rossiyanka in the Russian Championship. She is a member of the South African national team.
Abdullaziz Al-Dawsari is a Saudi football player. He currently plays for his country, Saudi Arabia, as well as Al-Hilal in the Saudi Professional League.
Emanuel Biancucchi Cuccitini is an Argentine football midfielder who plays for Brasileirão Série B club Ceará.

Henry Javier Hernández is a Colombian professional footballer who plays as a forward. He was ranked the third top goalscorer of the world in 2012 by IFFHS behind Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo, scoring 35 goals in 45 matches with Guatemalan club Heredia.
Julio Elías Musimessi was an Argentine football goalkeeper who played for Newell's Old Boys, Boca Juniors and the Argentina national team.

Mesut Özil is a German footballer who plays for English club Arsenal and the German national team. Özil has been a youth national team member since 2006, and a member of the German national team since 2009.
Ismail Easa is a Maldivian footballer nicknamed "Messi", who is currently playing for New Radiant Sports Club.

Gerardo Daniel "Tata" Martino is a former Argentine footballer who is currently the manager of the Argentine national team.
Martino played mostly for Newell's Old Boys in his native Rosario.

Lucas Scaglia is an Argentine footballer who plays as a midfielder for Jacksonville Armada FC in the North American Soccer League. He was one of three Argentinians signed by the team on January 29, 2015. He previously played for current Armada FC coach Guillermo Hoyo at Club Bolivar. He is a childhood friend of FC Barcelona forward Lionel Messi.
Nicolas Timmermans is a Belgian footballer who plays for Eupen in the Belgian Second Division.
Lorenzo Insigne is an Italian professional footballer who plays as a forward or attacking midfielder for Italian club Napoli and the Italy national team.

Indi Armstrong Cowie is a Scottish American professional freestyle footballer and football coach. She became an assistant coach to Anson Dorrance at the North Carolina Tar Heels when an anterior cruciate ligament injury caused her retirement from college soccer.
Ryan Gauld is a Scottish professional footballer who currently plays as an attacking midfielder for Portuguese club Sporting Clube de Portugal and the Scotland national under-21 football team.
Pau López Sabata, known simply as Pau, is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for RCD Espanyol as a goalkeeper.

Estefanía Romina Banini Ruíz is a Argentine football forward currently playing for American National Women's Soccer League club Washington Spirit. She previously spent four seasons with Colo-Colo of the Chilean women's football championship. Banini is a member of the Argentine women's national team.
Sergei Sergeyevich Yashin is a Russian footballer.

Michel François Platini is a football administrator, who served as the president of the Union of European Football Associations from 2007 until 2015, after which he was banned for 8 years following an ethics investigation by the FIFA Ethics Committee on 21 December 2015, and formerly a French football player and manager.
Michel Platini Ferreira Mesquita or simply Michel Platini is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Brasília.
François-Cyrille Grange is a French alpine skier who competed in the early 2000s.
Nils Lennart Johansson was the fifth and, to date, the longest serving president of UEFA, the Union of European Football Associations, from his election at UEFA's Malta Congress in 1990 until 2007.

Serge Chiesa is a former professional French footballer .
He is a historic player of Olympique Lyonnais, an excellent dribbler whose skill was comparable to Michel Platini.
Michel Hidalgo is a French former football player and manager. He was the coach of the French national team from 1976 to 1984.
Gérard Janvion is a retired French international footballer who played defender.
Robyn Ainsworth, was a 12-year-old schoolgirl and figure skater who lit the Olympic Flame in 1988 Winter Olympics.
Jean-François Larios, nicknamed "Turbo" is a retired football midfielder from France. He earned seventeen international caps for the French national team during the late 1970s and early 1980s.

Antonio Alzamendi Casas was a Uruguayan football player who retired in 1991.
His official debut was with the Uruguayan team Wanderers de Durazno. Alzamendi played for Uruguay at the 1986 and 1990 FIFA World Cups, scoring against West Germany in 1986.
Ivan Curkovic is a former Croatian and naturalized Serbian footballer, who played as a goalkeeper for Velež Mostar, Partizan and Saint-Étienne.
Rino Marchesi is a former Italian football midfielder and manager from San Giuliano Milanese.

Domenico Penzo is a retired Italian professional football player.
He played 6 seasons in the Serie A for A.S. Roma, Brescia Calcio, Hellas Verona F.C., Juventus F.C. and S.S.C. Napoli.
Christian Lopez is a French retired footballer who played as a defender.
Luís Carlos Almada Soares, commonly known as Platini, is a Cape Verdean footballer who plays for Egyptian club El Ittihad Alexandria as a winger.
John Nicholaas "Johnny" Rep is a former Dutch footballer. He currently holds the all-time record for FIFA World Cup goals for the Netherlands with 7.
Roberto Pruzzo is an Italian former football striker, now a coach. He currently is the Sports manager of Savona. He represented Italy at UEFA Euro 1980.

Ángel María Villar Llona is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a midfielder.
After having represented Athletic Bilbao during a full decade, he went on to serve an even larger stint as president of the Spanish Football Federation.

Amara Simba, Dakar, Senegal is a retired French football player. During his career he played for Paris SG, AS Cannes, AS Monaco, SM Caen and Lille OSC in France, Club Leon in Mexico and Leyton Orient, Kingstonian, Kettering Town, Barnet, St.
William Gaillard is the director of communications and public affairs for the Union of European Football Associations. He is also the Senior Advisor to the President of UEFA Michel Platini.

Franz Anton Beckenbauer is a German former professional footballer and manager. Early in his playing career he was nicknamed Der Kaiser because of his elegant style, dominance and leadership on the field, and also as his first name "Franz" is reminiscent of the Austrian emperors.
Susan Stahnke is a German TV presenter. She was born in Hamelin.
Beckenbauer Seur-In is a professional footballer from Thailand. He currently plays for Sriracha FC in the Thailand Division 1 League. He is named after Franz Beckenbauer.
Stephan Beckenbauer was a German footballer, the son of Franz Beckenbauer.
Miloud Hadefi was an Algerian football player and manager. Hedefi represented Algeria in two Football World Cup qualifying matches. His preferred position was Libero.

Gert Trinklein is a former German football player.
Between 1969 and 1978 Trinklein appeared in 230 matches for Eintracht Frankfurt. In 1979 he moved to the USA, becoming the third German soccer pro besides Franz Beckenbauer and Gerd Müller. Since 1985 he is an independent tradesman and merchandises at sport events. Since 2006 Gert Trinklein is part of the FDP fraction in Frankfurt parliament.

Heinz Gründel is a former German footballer.
Gründel played in his entire career 161 matches in the Bundesliga and scored 24 goals. The midfielder played for Germany on four occasions. In 1986 he was called up by then manager Franz Beckenbauer to the 26 men pre-squad for the World Cup in Mexico. Finally, he was cut out, together with later 1990 World Champion Guido Buchwald.
With Hamburger SV Gründel won the DFB-Pokal in 1987 winning 3–1 against Stuttgarter Kickers.
Hans-Joachim Fassnacht is a retired German swimmer. He competed at the 1968 and 1972 Summer Olympics in various freestyle and butterfly events and won a silver medal in the 4×200 m freestyle in 1972.
Pierluigi Cera is a former Italian footballer who played as a midfielder or as a defender, most notably for Cagliari, and the Italy national football team.
Josef Dieter "Sepp" Maier is a German former professional football goalkeeper. Regarded as one of Germany's greatest ever goalkeepers, his nickname was "Die Katze von Anzing" for his fast reflexes.
Yasin Özdenak is a former Turkish football goalkeeper and now an active coach. He is currently employed by Hume City FC as the Technical Director of the Club.

Werner Roth is a retired American professional football defender.
Mainly associated with the New York Cosmos, he also represented the United States men's national soccer team for three years. He is a member of the National Soccer Hall of Fame.

Michel Kitabdjian is a French former referee. He officiated at the 1975 European Cup Final between Leeds United and Bayern Munich, disallowing a goal by Leeds United's Peter Lorimer for offside and denying Leeds two penalty appeals as Franz Beckenbauer first handled the ball in the box and then brought down Allan Clarke in a tackle.
Nicolas Jüllich is a German footballer who currently plays for SG Sonnenhof Großaspach.
Anton Ondruš is a former Slovak football player and considered one of the best defenders of the seventies.

Gerhard Mayer-Vorfelder, often called "MV", was the Vice President of the Union of European Football Associations. Prior to his UEFA career, Mayer-Vorfelder was a politician of the Christian Democratic Union of Germany, and served in the state cabinet of Baden-Württemberg from 1976 to 1998.

José Francisco Jovel Cruz is a retired football player from El Salvador who represented his country at the 1982 FIFA World Cup in Spain.
His son Carlos Francisco Jovel Navas currently plays for Luís Ángel Firpo.

Wolfgang Overath is a former West German footballer. A true one-club man, Overath spent his entire professional career at 1. FC Köln. He represented his country three times in World Cup finals, culminating in 1974 with victory on home soil. Primarily a creative playmaker, Overath was known for his passing ability, technique and his left foot.

Ditmar Jakobs is a former German football player.
He was a centre-back, a classical libero in the mold of Franz Beckenbauer or Willi Schulz.
Gareth Frank Bale is a Welsh professional footballer who plays as a winger for Spanish club Real Madrid and the Wales national team.

Lehlohonolo Majoro is a South African football striker playing in the Premier Soccer League for Orlando Pirates He is one of the most consistent strikers, scoring over 10 goals in three consecutive seasons.

Harry Wilson is a Welsh professional footballer who plays as a winger for Premier League club Liverpool. In October 2013 Wilson became the youngest ever player to play for Wales, at the age of 16 years and 207 days, beating a record previously held by Gareth Bale.
Álvaro Medrán Just is a Spanish professional footballer who plays for Getafe CF on loan from Real Madrid as a midfielder.

Jack Topping is an English chorister who came to public attention during 2013 for his solo vocal performances. Topping comes from Liverpool and is a member of the choir of Liverpool Metropolitan Cathedral.
George Christopher Williams is a professional footballer who plays for Gillingham on loan from Fulham and the Wales national team.
Christopher "Chris" Pike is a Welsh former professional footballer. His clubs included Fulham, Cardiff City and Gillingham. He made over 250 Football League appearances.
Liliane Tannoury is a senior Lebanese TV presenter. She works as a sports anchor for Al Arabiya TV in Dubai.
Rebecca Angharad "Becky" James is a Welsh professional racing cyclist specialising in track cycling from Abergavenny, Wales. James was the 2013 world sprint and keirin champion.
George Lebese is a South African international footballer who plays professionally for Kaizer Chiefs, as a left winger.
Florentino Pérez Rodríguez is a Spanish businessman, civil engineer, former politician, and current president of Real Madrid, as well as Grupo ACS, a civil engineering company.
Franco Baldini is a former Italian footballer and former technical director for English Premier League club Tottenham Hotspur.

Damien Comolli is a former football coach, scout and director of football. He has previously worked with AS Monaco, AS Saint-Étienne, Arsenal, Tottenham Hotspur and Liverpool. He speaks fluent English, Spanish and French.
Mika Chunuonsee is a Welsh-Thai footballer who plays as a Defender for Thai Premier League club Bangkok United.
Jürgen Damm Rascón is a Mexican professional footballer who plays as a right winger for Liga MX club Tigres UANL and Mexico national team.

David Owen Vaughan /'v???n/ is a Welsh footballer who plays for Championship club Nottingham Forest. He plays as a midfielder.
Vaughan previously played for Crewe Alexandra, where he spent seven years between 2000 and 2007.
Paul George Barron is an English former football goalkeeper. He is currently the head coach for the Las Vegas Mobsters
Duncan Ian Watmore is an English professional footballer who plays for Sunderland. Watmore has also previously played for Altrincham, Clitheroe and Hibernian.

Ali Adnan Kadhim Nassir Al-Tameemi, is an Iraqi professional footballer who plays as a left back for Italian club Udinese. Ali Adnan also won the 2013 Asian Young Footballer of the Year, and is often referred to as "Asia's Gareth Bale"or the "Iraqi Roberto Carlos".
